3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: More auditions from Copenhagen and Aarhus.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: The three groups of contestants gather for boot camps at Puk Studio, Hotel Marienlyst and Dragsholm Slot, and each group is reduced to five.

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: Boot camps continue, and the number of contestants in each group is cut to three.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: First live show, featuring songs from the Tjeklisten chart.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: The contestants perform with the DR Big Band.

11.title: Episode #1.11
11.plot: Singer Anne Linnet guests the show, and the contestants sing her songs as well as Elvis Presley songs.

12.title: Episode #1.12
12.plot: James Blunt guest stars, and the contestants sing his songs as well as the judges' choices.

13.title: Episode #1.13
13.plot: The finale with the last two contestants performing the viewers' favourite song, their own choice and the newly composed winner's song. Also features live reports from the final two's home towns and two all-star performances by the nine finalists and by contestants eliminated in earlier rounds.

14.title: X Factor Special
14.plot: An X Factor Special offering highlights of the first season, unaired footage and details of what happened after the finale.

1.title: Episode #2.1
1.plot: The judges arrive at DR Byen and kick off the Copenhagen auditions.

4.title: Episode #2.4
4.plot: More auditions, and it's announced which judge will get which group of contestants.

5.title: Episode #2.5
5.plot: Contestants gather for boot camps at Tisvildeleje Strandhotel, Lykkesholm Slot and the Hilton, and each group is cut to five. Remee has problems finding groups he likes and arranges to pick his own group from Blachman's rejects.

6.title: Episode #2.6
6.plot: Boot camps continue, and the number of contestants in each group is cut to three.

7.title: Episode #2.7
7.plot: The nine finalists perform in the first live-show, and the song theme is simple: Hits.

8.title: Episode #2.8
8.plot: Made in Denmark: The contestants perform Danish hit songs.

12.title: Episode #2.12
12.plot: Semifinal night: Sanne Salomonsen guest stars, and the contestants sing her songs and also select a song of their own choice to dedicate to a loved one.

13.title: Episode #2.13
13.plot: The finale: The final three competitors perform a song of their own choice, and one of them is eliminated. The final two perform the newly composed winner's song. Also, reports from the finalists' home towns, all-star performances by the nine finalists and by contestants eliminated in earlier rounds, and appearances by last year's winner Martin and British pop band Take That.

3.title: Episode #3.3
3.plot: Final auditions from Copenhagen and Aarhus.

4.title: Episode #3.4
4.plot: Elimation round at Koncerthuset in Copenhagen.

5.title: Episode #3.5
5.plot: Each group of contestants gather for boot camps at Steengaard Herregård, Bernstorff Slot and Molskroen, and each judge starts eliminations aided by guest judges.

6.title: Episode #3.6
6.plot: Boot camps continue as each judge chooses his or her final three contestants.

imdb.plot outline: Premiering in January 2008, the Danish version of X Factor quickly became a major success for public broadcaster DR. The disagreements of the judging panel and particularly the antics of Thomas Blachman made newspaper headlines, and the Friday night competition was shattered. The first season opened with three episodes of auditions in Copenhagen and Aarhus. The contestants were split into three groups selected and mentored by one judge each: 15 to 25 years old, over 25, and groups. Two episodes of boot camp eliminations followed. The nine selected acts then competed in eight live shows with one or more musical themes, with the contestant and their mentor choosing their song and facing the judges' comments and the viewers' votes. One contestant was eliminated each week, first with the judges choosing between the bottom two, later based exclusively on the votes.
imdb.title: X Factor
plot: Danish version of the _X Factor_ (qv) format, promoted as the ultimate talent show.::Peter Brandt Nielsen

Premiering in January 2008, the Danish version of _X Factor_ (qv) quickly became a major success for public broadcaster DR. The disagreements of the judging panel and particularly the antics of Thomas Blachman made newspaper headlines, and the Friday night competition was shattered. The first season opened with three episodes of auditions in Copenhagen and Aarhus. The contestants were split into three groups selected and mentored by one judge each: 15 to 25 years old, over 25, and groups. Two episodes of boot camp eliminations followed. The nine selected acts then competed in eight live shows with one or more musical themes, with the contestant and their mentor choosing their song and facing the judges' comments and the viewers' votes. One contestant was eliminated each week, first with the judges choosing between the bottom two, later based exclusively on the votes.::Peter Brandt Nielsen
